Questions:
Which of the following is considered the experimental procedure in the THRIVE Smart study?
A) Standard chemotherapy treatment with Capecitabine (Xeloda);
B) Use of a smart pill bottle to monitor medication adherence and trigger clinical alerts;
C) Completing standard medical history and physical exams;
D) Receiving standard oncology care and follow-up appointments.

Correct answer: B

What alternative options are available to you if you decide not to participate in the THRIVE Smart study?
A) You can opt for regular clinic visits without the use of a smart pill bottle; 
B) You will be provided with a different type of medication adherence technology;
C) There are no alternative options mentioned in the study consent form;
D) You will be enrolled in a different study focused on oral chemotherapy adherence.

Correct answer: C

Who is authorized to use and/or disclose your Protected Health Information (PHI) for the THRIVE Smart study?
A) Only the Principal Investigator and the research staff;
B) The Principal Investigator, research staff, Winship Cancer Institute of Emory University, NRG Oncology, and associated administrative personnel;
C) Any healthcare provider in the United States;
D) Only the funding sources, Developmental Funds from the Winship Cancer Institute of Emory University and NRG Oncology.

Correct answer: B
